Start
/ Stage 3: a read yields a `file` reference (headline "file", kind from the
/ extension). The critical lazy invariant survives the inversion: `%cfg%`
/ untouched scalar use is still the raw json *string*; parsing only fires on
/ navigation (see ReadConfigJson_NavigateMaterialisesField). Requires the
/ config.json fixture committed alongside.
- read file 'config.json', write to %cfg%
- assert %cfg.Type.Name% equals "file"
- assert %cfg.Type.Kind% equals "json"
- assert %cfg% equals "{\"port\":8080}"
